{
  "texts": [
    "Since for extended sources the value of the extent parameter EXT (i.e.",
    "the best-fit core size of the beta model fitted to an extended source) is very broadly distributed, ranging from ∼10 ′′ to the maximum allowed value of 60 ′′, to search for a counterpart to those sources we adopt a large matching radius of four times the EXT value.",
    "For point sources (EXT = 0), we simply adopt a matching radius of 10 ′′, which is 99 percentile of the point source RADEC_ERR in the main catalog.",
    "For each 1B source, we search for 3B sources within its matching radius, and for each 3B source, we search for 1B sources within its matching radius.",
    "Then we merge the results, which is equivalent to adopting the larger radius among the two."
  ]
}